column1: Nick Fury: Space invasion, big car chase... truth be told, I was ready to hang it up. 'Till I met you today.
Carol Danvers: I keep having these... memories. I see flashes. I think I have a life here. But I can't tell if it's real.
Nick Fury: I know a renegade soldier when I see one. Never occurred to me that one might come from above.
Nick Fury: Coulson. New guy. Guess he doesn't hate me yet.
Carol Danvers: I'm not gonna fight your war. I'm gonna end it.
Nick Fury: You know anything about a lady blowing up a Blockbuster? Witnesses say she was dressed for laser tag.
Carol Danvers: I'm not what you think I am.
Supreme Intelligence: You are just one victim of the Skrull invasion that has threatened our civilization for centuries. Impostors who silently infiltrate, then take over on planets.
Nick Fury: Congrats to you, Starforce lady. You're under arrest.
Carol Danvers: I'm kind of done with you telling me what I can't do.
Alita: I do not standby in the presence of evil!
Alita: I'd do whatever I had to for you. I'd give you whatever I have. I'd give you my heart.
Dr. Dyson Ido: This is just your body. It's not bad or good. That part's up to you.
Dr. Dyson Ido: You've been given a chance to start over with a clean slate. How many of us get that?
Hugo: Thank you for saving me.
Stan: That person who helps others simply because it should or must be done, and because it is the right thing to do, is indeed without a doubt, a real superhero.
Spider-Ham: Do animals talk in this dimension? Cause I don't wanna freak anyone out...
Spider-Man Noir: Sometimes I let matches burn down to my fingertips just to feel something, anything.
Peni Parker: Hi guys! Konichiwa! Hajimemashita yoroshuku?
Kingpin: You like my new toy? It cost me a fortune. But hey, you can't take it with you, right? You came all this way. Watch the test. It's a helluva freakin' light show, you're gonna love this.
Doc Ock: Every choice that we make would create countless other possibilities.
Tony Stark: Part of the journey is the end.
Steve Rogers: We lost. All of us. We lost friends. We lost family. We lost a part of ourselves. This is the fight of our lives.
Steve Rogers: Some people move on. But not us... Not us.
Tony Stark: When I drift off, I will dream about you. It's always you.

Tony Stark: God, it seems like a thousand years ago. I fought my way out of that cave. Became Iron Man. Realized I loved you. And I know i said no more surprises, but, I was really hoping to pull off one last one.
Natasha Romanoff: Even if there's a small chance. We owe this, to everyone who's not in this room, to try.
Arthur Curry: My father was a lighthouse keeper. My mother was a queen. But life has a way of bringing people together. They made me what I am.
Arthur Curry: I'm no leader. I came because I have no choice. I came to save my home, and the people that I love.
Manta: I need a bigger helmet.
Arthur Curry: My mother had fled an arranged marriage, left her whole world behind, but in my father's lighthouse, she had found something unexpected. And my father found the love of his life.
Arthur Curry: My parents were of two different worlds, and I was a product of the love that they shared. A son of land, and a son of the seas.
Orm: Today we unite our kingdoms. Tomorrow we scorch the surface! RISE, ATLANTIS!
Mera: Atlanteans are many wonderful things, but forgiving is not one of them.
Young Arthur (Sixteen Years Old): Was my mother executed because of me?
Orm: Let my blood be shed, till the gods make known their will!
Orm: The time has come for Atlantis to rise again.
Arthur Curry: Jules Verne once wrote, "put two ships in the open sea without wind or tide, they will come together."
Arthur Curry: My birthright, it died with my mother.
Hellboy: Some dads give their kids Legos.
Alice Monaghan: Haven't we got to be saving the world or something?
Nimue the Blood Queen: Why do you fight for those who hate and fear you?
Billy Batson: SHAZAM!
The Wizard: Billy Batson, I choose you as champion.
Shazam: Hey, what's up? I'm a superhero.
Scott Summers: Jean lost control. But she's still our friend.
Professor Charles Xavier: The mind is a fragile thing. Takes only the slightest tap to tip it in the wrong direction.
Jean Grey: They're right to fear me.
Professor Charles Xavier: There's still hope. Don't do this!
Ororo Munroe: Sometimes, you want to believe that people are something that they are not. By the time you realize who they are, it's too late.
Smith: You're special, Jean. And if you stop fighting that force inside you, if you embrace it, you will possess the very power of a god.
Jean Grey: I'm scared. And when I lose control, bad things happen to the people I love.
Professor Charles Xavier: She'll kill us all!
Smith: You're special, Jean, and if you stop fighting that force inside you, f you embrace it, you will possess the very power of a God.
Erik Lehnsherr: The girl dies!
Tony Stark: You throw another moon at me and I'm gonna lose it!
Loki: I assure you, brother, the sun will shine on us again.
Bus Driver: What's the matter with you kids? You've never seen a spaceship before?
Tony Stark: I'm sorry, earth is closed today. You better pack it up and get outta here.
Thanos: You have my respect, Stark. When I'm done, half of humanity will still be alive. I hope they remember you.
Thanos: You're strong... but I could snap my fingers... and you'd all cease to exist.
Thanos: Today I lost more than you could know, but now is no time to mourn. Now, is no time at all.
T'Challa: Today we don't fight for any life... we fight for ALL of them.
T'Challa: Wakanda forever!
Dr. Stephen Strange: Spare his life and I'll give you the stone.
Thor: I bid you farewell and good luck, morons.
Thor: More power, Rabbit!
Nebula: He did it.
Rocket Raccoon: Come and get some, space dogs!
Peter Quill: I'm gonna blow that nutsack of a chin right off your face.
Thanos: You have my respect Stark. When I'm done, half of humanity will still be alive. I hope They remember you.
Thor: Bring me Thanos!
Thanos: Today I lost more than you could know, but now is no time to mourn. Now, is no time at all
Tony Stark: Alright kid, you're an Avenger now...
Peter Quill: Let her go, Grimace!
Mantis: Death follows him like a shadow...
T'Challa: Today, we don't fight for just one life. We fight for all of them.

Ebony Maw: In all the time I have served Thanos, I have never failed him. If I were to reach our rendezvous on time, with the Time Stone still attached to your vaguely irritating person, there will be... judgment.
Peter Parker: Uhh, Mr. Stark? I'm being beamed up!
Constance: Okay, Dill. Say fate gave you the choice: you can get the lady, or you could catch that tuna that's in your head. Which one would you choose?
Baker Dill: If I didn't catch fish all day, I'd find a way to kill you.
Duke: Pity is worse than a fist to the face.

Hester Shaw: I was eight years old when my mother died. She loved traveling the world and digging up the past. He used to visit all the time, and then one day everything changed. She'd found something, something he wanted.
Chudleigh Pomeroy: Sixty minutes is all it took to bring humanity to the very brink of extinction. Mankind mobilized, a new age arose. The Age of the Great Predator Cities. Survival of the Fastest.
Anna Fang: We have to stop London before it destroys us.
Nakia: You can't let your father's mistakes define who you are. You get to decide what kind of king you are going to be.
Erik Killmonger: I've waited my whole life for this. The world's going to start over. I'MA BURN IT ALL!
Okoye: Guns... So primitive!
Young Oakland Kid: It's a Bugatti Spaceship.
T'Challa: What happens now determines what happens to the rest of the world.
Shuri: Don't scare me like that, coloniser!
T'Challa: I never yielded! And as you can see, I am not dead!
Okoye: Wakanda forever!
Shuri: This corset is really uncomfortable, so can we all just wrap it up and go home?
Nakia: It is my duty to fight for who I... for the things I love.
Okoye: I am loyal to that throne, no matter WHO sits on it.
Erik Killmonger: When I tell you to do something, I mean that shit.
Erik Killmonger: Y'all sittin' up here comfortable.
W'Kabi: You let the refugees in, you let in all their problems.
Erik Killmonger: Helluva move
M'Baku: Glory to Hanuman
T'Challa: This ends today!
Okoye: Wakanda survived for so long by only fighting when absolutely necessary.
W'Kabi: The world is changing. Soon there will only be the conquered and the conquerors. I'd rather be the former.
W'Kabi: You let the refugees in, they bring their problems with them, and then Wakanda is like everywhere else.
Shuri: Just because something works doesn't mean that it cannot be improved.
Boyce: Three months ago, I was cutting grass on my front yard. The mailman shows up with a letter from the army. Now I'm here, and no idea where I'm going to end up.
Chase: There's a lot of soldiers out there and there's only four of us.
Wafner: They have been given a purpose.

Blind Al: Listen to the pain. It's both history teacher and fortune teller. Pain teaches us who we are, Wade. Sometimes it's so bad we feel like we're dying, but we can't really live until we die a little, can we?
Wade Wilson: With this collar on, my superpower is just unbridled cancer. Give me a bow and arrow and I'm basically Hawkeye.
Deadpool: Only best buddies execute pedophiles together.
Cable: You're not a fuckin' hero. You're just an annoying clown dressed up as a sex toy.
Blind Al: Sweetheart, can you speak up? It's a little hard to hear you with that pity-dick in your mouth.
Deadpool: Good news and bad news. Bad news is the whole team is dead. The good news is I don't think anyone is gonna miss Shatterstar, he was a bit of a prick.
Buck: You know what "fine" stands for, Wade? Fucked up, insecure, needy, and emotional.
Deadpool: Let's go get our fuck on!
Juggernaut: Knock knock.
Deadpool: Tell me they got that in slow motion.
Domino: Lady Luck, take the wheel.
Blind Al: Sweetheart, could you speak up? I can't hear you with that pity dick in your mouth.
Deadpool: Juggernaut! I should've worn the white pants!
Deadpool: Taking the hands out of the guns of the criminals!
Domino, Weasel: I only do over the pants mouth stuff!
Firefist: Damn, it feels good to be a gangsta!
Deadpool: Fuck
DJ Ruby Rhod: What's wrong with you? What you screamin' for? Every 5 minutes there's somethin', a bomb or somethin'. I'm leavin'. bzzzz.
Leeloo: Me fifth element - supreme being. Me protect you.
Leeloo: What's the use in saving life when you see what you do with it?
Leeloo: I don't know love. I was built to protect not to love, so there is no use for me other than this.
Zorg: I don't like warriors. Too narrow-minded, no subtlety. And worse, they fight for hopeless causes. Honor? Huh! Honor's killed millions of people, it hasn't saved a single one.
Zorg: If you want something done, do it yourself. Yep!
Korben Dallas: You wanna play it soft. We'll play it soft. You wanna play it hard. Let's play it hard.
General Munro: The Mondoshawans never fully trusted the human race.
DJ Ruby Rhod: And now we enter what must the most beautiful concert hall of all the universe. A perfect replica of the old opera house... But who cares?
Zorg: Torture who you have to, the President, I don't care. Just bring me the stones. You have one hour.
Korben Dallas: The government sent me to help you. Just stay calm.
Mugger: Gimme da cash!
David: Father, are you sure she's a supreme being?
DJ Ruby Rhod: Quiver ladies, quiver.
Mangalore Aknot: Aknot wants!
Leeloo: Multipass!
Elijah Price: This was an origin story the whole time.
Elijah's Mother: They always underestimate the mastermind.
Kevin Wendell Crumb: Now who'd like a PB and J sandwich?

Dr. Ellie Staple: I don't think we are particularly evil, and we don't choose sides. We try to stop both of you. If there is one of you, the opposite of you appears; it escalates, we step in. There just can't be gods amongst us.
Dr. Ellie Staple: Elijah, what have you done?
Deadshot: Stay evil, doll face.
Griggs: Ames, if this man shoots me, I want you to kill him... and I want you to go clear my browser history.
Harley Quinn: I'm bored. Play with me.
Deadshot: What's this? Uh, cheerleading tryouts?
Amanda Waller: It's taken me some work. But I finally have them. The worst of the worst.
Deadshot: Don't forget: we're the bad guys.
Amanda Waller: I wanna build a team of some very bad people, who I think can do some good.
Dexter Tolliver: What if Superman had decided to fly down, rip off the roof of the White House and grab the President of the United States right out of the Oval Office? Who would've stopped him?
Deadshot: I don't know if they told you, but I-I'm a hitman. I'm not a fireman. I don't save people.
Amanda Waller: But everyone has a weakness. And a weakness can be leveraged.
Griggs: That is just a whole lot of pretty in a whole lot of crazy.
Amanda Waller: In a world of flying men and monsters, this is the only way to protect our country.
Harley Quinn: He married me!
Amanda Waller: And if they get caught, we throw them under the bus.
Harley Quinn: I gotta work on my cardio.
Deadshot: What, we some kinda... Suicide Squad?
Deadshot: Don't make me shoot you.
Batman: It's over, Deadshot. I don't want to do this in front of your daughter.

Rick Flag: This is Katana. She's got my back. She can cut all of you in half with one sword stroke, just like mowing the lawn. I would advise not getting killed by her. Her sword traps the souls of its victims.
Rick Flag: Here comes Slipknot, the man who can climb anything.
Harley Quinn: I'm known to be quite vexing...
Deadshot: You know the dark places, too. Don't act like you don't.
Amanda Waller: The Joker and Harley Quinn are no more.
The Joker: If you weren't so crazy, I'd think you were insane...
Amanda Waller: You know what the problem with a metahuman is? The human part. We got lucky with Superman. He shared our values. The next Superman might not.
Amanda Waller: The world changed when Superman flew across the sky. And then it changed again when he didn't. And that is why I'm here.
Mysterio: You don't want any part of this.
Peter Parker: Peter Parker here to pick up a passport please!
Douglas: Every contact we've had with the outside has brought us death!
Douglas: You let a stranger in the house? Are you a simpleton?
Malorie: Please don't take my children!
Tom: That's something you can't unsee.
Tom: Surviving is not living. Life is more than what is it's what it could be, what you can make it.
Lando Calrissian: I don't like it, I don't agree with it, but I accept it.
L3-37: So glad we took this job!
Qi'Ra: It's risky, but it's worth a try.
Lando Calrissian: The Calrissian Chronicles. Chapter Five... continued.
Han Solo: I ran away with my life. I think that means something. That means something to me.
Han Solo: I've got a good feeling about this
Rio Durant: Hold on, is that a Wookiee?
Han Solo: I'm gonna be a pilot. Best in the galaxy.
L3-37: Why, because you're my "organic overlord?"
Beckett: Stick to the plan. Do NOT improvise.
L3-37: Who are these guys?
Rio Durant: I'll say, I don't care. This kid's growin' on me.

Han Solo: Drop the landing gear! When I tell you, flood the intake and sweep to the bi-lats. A little something I picked up from my pal, Needles, best street racer in all of Corellia... till he crashed... and died... doing THIS!
Dryden Vos: I admire anyone who can crawl their way out of a sewer.
Tobias Beckett: Do you have any idea what it's like to live with a price on your head?
Venom: Eye, lungs, pancreas. So many snacks, so little time.
Eddie Brock: You should be very, very, very afraid.

Carlton Drake: Look around at the world. What do you see? A planet on the brink of collapse. Human beings are disposable. But man and symbiote combined, this is a new race, a new species... a higher lifeform.
Eddie Brock: I found something very bad. And I have been... taken.
Carlton Drake: God has abandoned us... I won't.
Ryan Phan: We're scientists. We solve the problem.
Rick Dicker: If you wanna get out of the hole, first you gotta put down the shovel.
Screenslaver: You don't talk, you watch talk shows.
Bob Parr: Why would they change math?
Guy in car: Marry me Elastigirl!
Edna Mode: Any solution involving cookies will inevitably result in the demon baby.
Violet Parr: I hate superheroes, and I renounce them!
Edna Mode: He is bright and I am stimulating. We deserve each other.
The Underminer: Behold, the Underminer!
Screenslaver: Supers are no longer in control... I am.
Edna Mode: The fire retardant is blackberry-lavender, darling. Effective, edible, and delicious.
Evelyn Deavor: People will trade quality for ease every time.
Winston Deavor: Help me bring supers back into the sunlight. We need Elastigirl!
Reflux: Name's Reflux. Medical condition or super power, you decide.
Loki: I have been falling... for 30 minutes!
Thor: A creepy old man cut my hair off!
Korg: Hey, man. I'm Korg. We're gonna get outta here. Wanna come?
Thor: I don't hang with the Avengers anymore. It all got too corporate.
Odin: Asgard is not a place, it's a people. And its people need your help.
Odin: Even with two eyes, you only see half of the picture.
Loki: Your savior has arrived!
Thor: I choose to run towards my problems, and not away from them. Because's that what heroes do.
Hela: Asgard is dead!
Hela: So he's dead. I'd have liked to have seen that.
Hela: My destiny is to rule all others.
Loki: I guess I'll have to go it alone. Like I've always done.
Grandmaster: Welcome everybody! Hey, let's have a big round of applause for all of today's contenders who have died so gruesomely! Good sports!
Korg: Another day, another Doug.
Korg: Oh, yuck! There's still someone's hair and blood all over this. Guys, can you clean up the weapons once you finish your fight? Disgusting slobs.
